<subSubSection id="C3046513FFDEFFDDFEDAA31B2CFBA983" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA13698FFDEFFDDFEDAA31B2CFBA983" blockId="25.[264,1325,719,1745]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFDEFFDDFEDAA31B2FC9A90A" box="[312,414,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFDEFFDDFE52A31B2C62A90A" box="[432,565,1599,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ankusha">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFDEFFDDFE52A31B2C62A90A" box="[432,565,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. ankusha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFDEFFDDFC7FA31B2A40A90A" box="[925,1047,1599,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFDEFFDDFC7FA31B2A40A90A" box="[925,1047,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Xenovarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having entire, conically produced pygophore and spatulate, medially twisted aedeagal shaft. It is not closely related to any of the included species in the genus though it shares the characters of the male pygophore with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFDEFFDDFDEAA3932CF2A982" box="[520,677,1719,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressa">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFDEFFDDFDEAA3932CF2A982" box="[520,677,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. compressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
